48:39.240 --> 48:40.740
Did they say X, Y, Z?

48:40.980 --> 48:42.420
Naval intelligence.

48:42.600 --> 48:42.820
Okay.

48:42.820 --> 48:46.700
Um, uh, the, the Kennedy, uh, connection.

48:47.240 --> 48:48.280
Around UFOs.

48:48.280 --> 48:48.440
Yeah.

48:48.440 --> 48:48.900
His assassin.

48:49.100 --> 48:49.300
Yeah.

48:49.300 --> 48:51.340
His assassination being linked to UFOs.

48:51.340 --> 48:54.140
Although, but definitely the Kennedy and UFOs were correct.

48:54.300 --> 48:55.660
And, and that was a huge part of the dark skies.

48:55.660 --> 48:57.140
Did he go deeper on that at all?

48:57.320 --> 48:58.400
No, I don't think so.

48:58.420 --> 49:02.320
I think he just sort of confirmed that that was, I mean, cause that's the essence of the

49:02.320 --> 49:03.220
dark skies pilot.

49:03.420 --> 49:03.720
Okay.

49:03.720 --> 49:10.080
And so as a consequence, the mere fact that we would say it in 1996, uh, today you can go

49:10.080 --> 49:12.180
on the internet, you find a lot of people talking about it.

49:12.280 --> 49:14.180
Malgrim certainly talked about it.

49:14.180 --> 49:15.680
He said, I think it was the number one issue.

49:15.800 --> 49:16.040
Correct.

49:16.340 --> 49:16.520
Yeah.

49:16.720 --> 49:19.740
But none of that existed when we put it in the pilot.

49:19.880 --> 49:23.800
The only reason we put it in the pilot is when we were sort of creating the show, we

49:23.800 --> 49:27.540
said, well, I'll tell you what, let's take the two greatest conspiracies of all time,

49:27.640 --> 49:29.740
UFOs and JFK.

49:29.880 --> 49:32.820
Let's put them in an atom collider and see what we get.

49:32.920 --> 49:34.480
And that's what dark skies was.

49:34.600 --> 49:37.820
So it wasn't us saying we have inside information.

49:37.820 --> 49:42.800
It was just saying, wouldn't this be interesting, but they sort of confirmed that we were on

49:42.800 --> 49:44.740
the right track with that, which is weird.

49:45.020 --> 49:48.760
And the reason I was asking him about body, Betty and Barney is they're in the pilot.

49:48.760 --> 49:54.840
Um, you know, the whole idea of majestic 12, uh, I don't recall that they actually, that

49:54.840 --> 49:59.820
this guy confirmed the name majestic 12, but he certainly the idea that there was naval

49:59.820 --> 50:07.680
intelligence involved in a, uh, a pretty vast and powerful organization that was dedicated

50:07.680 --> 50:08.520
to man.

50:08.660 --> 50:12.200
I think the term was managing the whole thing.

50:12.460 --> 50:17.900
It almost feels like, uh, that MJ 12 is like, they're like managing reality itself.

50:18.140 --> 50:18.480
Yeah.

50:18.480 --> 50:22.320
And, uh, and, uh, and managing timelines or something.

50:22.720 --> 50:26.220
And, and, and, and, oh, I, there's actually, there's, there is one thing we should point

50:26.220 --> 50:26.480
out.

50:26.600 --> 50:30.620
Um, the, the one thing, and I know we're going to talk later maybe about disclosure day

50:30.620 --> 50:35.340
because disclosure is a big theme, uh, of the, of the moment, but that's what dark skies

50:35.340 --> 50:35.840
was about.

50:35.960 --> 50:37.060
We had two characters.

50:37.200 --> 50:41.300
We had the young kid and his so-called boss slash mentor.

50:41.300 --> 50:45.520
And the entire series was like a tone poem between these two.

50:45.640 --> 50:48.320
One of them said the people have a right to know.

50:48.660 --> 50:52.900
And the other guy said the people can't handle the truth, sort of the Jack Nicholson statement.

50:53.360 --> 50:57.100
And so every episode kind of talked about that kind of thing.

50:57.380 --> 51:05.280
Anyway, in terms of disclosure, uh, back when they, they invoked the idea that, uh, and I'm

51:05.280 --> 51:09.960
sure you're, you've talked about it on your show, the, the idea of the, um, the aviary,

51:09.960 --> 51:12.100
which sort of came out in the eighties.

51:12.500 --> 51:14.680
These guys said, well, you've heard of the aviary.

51:14.680 --> 51:17.200
And that had been on that TV show, of course.

51:17.700 --> 51:20.200
And, um, they said, well, we're the aquarium.

51:20.380 --> 51:26.100
And now I've told that to people and I see you, you've got a smile on it because I've told

51:26.100 --> 51:30.460
it to people and they, they're like, yeah, I don't know about, but all Brent and I can

51:30.460 --> 51:32.700
do is bear witness to what was said.

51:32.800 --> 51:36.460
We can't evaluate, you know, the truth of that per se.

51:36.460 --> 51:42.620
For context, the aviary was this long rumored, uh, like it was like bird code names assigned

51:42.620 --> 51:47.320
to kind of disinfo agents around UFO related truths.

51:47.560 --> 51:53.380
So people like Rick Doty, John Lear, uh, it's kind of associated with Bill Moore and the

51:53.380 --> 51:54.900
agents where he made that MUFON speech.

51:55.000 --> 52:00.380
And he was like, I was, I took this Faustian bargain and was like led astray on this topic.

52:00.700 --> 52:04.720
So the one thing that they were confirming though, I mean, the one basic thing they were

52:04.720 --> 52:11.920
confirming is that, uh, the UFO topic, such as it was being managed in terms of what people

52:11.920 --> 52:16.120
were going to be allowed to know or not know air force, definitely not in favor of it.

52:16.360 --> 52:22.060
Air force holding the line, you know, closed down blue book in 69 said, we're washing our

52:22.060 --> 52:22.540
hands of that.

52:22.620 --> 52:24.040
We don't want any more to do about that.

52:24.360 --> 52:27.840
And their attitude was, well, obviously we think differently.

52:27.840 --> 52:34.020
The people we work with think, and I think Brent used the term slow drip disclosure, right?

52:34.440 --> 52:36.580
We know something has to change.

52:37.380 --> 52:37.760
Makes sense.

52:37.920 --> 52:42.400
I mean, uh, the Navy is really responsible for a lot of modern disclosure.

52:42.540 --> 52:47.120
Not only were the, all the sightings in those, that New York times article, Naval sightings.

52:47.240 --> 52:47.660
Right on.

52:47.660 --> 52:54.900
But you had, uh, Bray was the guy who like, you know, disclosed, I think in 20 and 20, 21,

52:55.420 --> 52:58.980
like that was the Navy that, you know, it was like, these were, these were how many sightings

52:58.980 --> 52:59.660
we had.

52:59.660 --> 53:02.840
And, you know, so a lot of these were actually like, you know, unidentified.

53:02.840 --> 53:06.100
I think Stratton was former Navy maybe as well.

53:06.100 --> 53:10.560
And he formed the whole UAP task force, which was basically like, let's internally review

53:10.560 --> 53:12.100
all of the data here.

53:12.100 --> 53:17.900
So yeah, the Navy feels like, uh, they hold the deeper stuff, the deeper secret.

53:18.000 --> 53:22.900
And what's interesting is that they were picking up on that detail because that film I told

53:22.900 --> 53:26.840
you that I had done for the sci-fi channel, kind of similar to dark skies.

53:26.840 --> 53:32.320
I mean, in structure kind of thing, but it was the air force in, um, in official denial.

53:32.320 --> 53:37.400
So we pivoted to Navy after, because we were talking about the Harrington story and we went,

53:37.520 --> 53:38.940
well, it can't hurt.

53:39.040 --> 53:39.700
Let's go Navy.

53:39.700 --> 53:45.180
There is one thing that he did say, I guess you should lay the vial on the table here.

53:46.000 --> 53:52.480
So there was a whole thing where we, again, he didn't answer a lot of our questions other

53:52.480 --> 53:55.040
than with terse, like, I don't have time for this.

53:55.340 --> 53:58.560
So we said, okay, well, what is it that you want to talk about?

53:58.640 --> 54:02.820
Like you're here to tell us, you know, what's the deal?

54:02.860 --> 54:05.300
It's, it's access for influence, right?

54:05.560 --> 54:07.680
You're going to, you want to influence our show.

54:07.800 --> 54:08.900
What do we get access to?

54:08.900 --> 54:09.740
What's the information?

54:10.580 --> 54:12.480
And he said, okay, here's this thing.

54:13.240 --> 54:14.420
It's all about the moon.

54:14.420 --> 54:21.280
He, well, he put, he put a vial on the table and you may be seeing them about that big,

54:21.280 --> 54:25.300
a little glass vial with a little black screw top on it.

54:25.760 --> 54:28.100
People, scientists use them in labs and things like that.

54:28.160 --> 54:31.420
So he put that on the table and said, it's all about that.

54:31.420 --> 54:37.440
And so when we picked it up, well, we each got a slightly different view of it.

54:37.480 --> 54:39.200
I, well, you saw it first.

54:39.580 --> 54:40.160
So I picked it up.

54:40.260 --> 54:42.280
Well, first of all, so he says it's all about the moon.

54:42.280 --> 54:45.640
And he's also bringing this up because they've seen our show Bible.

54:45.640 --> 54:51.020
And in the second season, we go, we deal with the, the space program.

54:51.020 --> 54:51.280
Right.

54:51.360 --> 54:51.540
Right.

54:51.760 --> 54:53.600
And he was like, you've got to move all that up.

54:54.460 --> 54:58.600
So already we're getting a taste of, they're going to tell us like when to write and how

54:58.600 --> 54:59.600
to write and all this other stuff.

54:59.600 --> 55:02.520
So what we were going to do in the second season, just so you know, is we were going

55:02.520 --> 55:05.540
to do season, we're going to go decade by decade every season.

55:05.760 --> 55:07.460
So the first season was the sixties.

55:07.600 --> 55:13.000
So in the second season, there was going to be an Apollo 18, even though that mission

55:13.000 --> 55:13.660
got canceled.

55:13.880 --> 55:14.060
Right.

55:14.140 --> 55:14.740
So we were going to.

55:14.760 --> 55:15.580
That was our dark skies.

55:15.580 --> 55:19.900
Now people have now speculated and done movies about that, but back then that's what we were

55:19.900 --> 55:20.400
going to do.

55:20.520 --> 55:24.120
So he knew that we were going moon forward.

55:24.220 --> 55:24.400
Right.

55:24.480 --> 55:27.020
And his whole point is forget about all this other stuff.

55:27.080 --> 55:27.900
It's all about the moon.

55:27.900 --> 55:29.760
And he slams this little vial down.

55:29.940 --> 55:30.480
I pick it up.

55:30.540 --> 55:34.620
I look at it and I'm like, and I shake it like it's a snow globe, but there's no liquid

55:34.620 --> 55:35.040
in it.

55:35.080 --> 55:40.200
And all of the, it's like gold flakes, except it looks like fool's gold because actual gold

55:40.200 --> 55:41.760
doesn't really look that gold.

55:41.900 --> 55:42.620
It's like more dull.

55:42.980 --> 55:44.860
Fool's gold is more, looks like gold.

55:44.980 --> 55:48.620
So it looks like these, looks like these gold flakes and they, everything just kind of

55:48.620 --> 55:50.860
floats, but there's no liquid.

55:51.180 --> 55:52.260
What do you think he meant by that?

55:52.300 --> 55:54.480
It's all about the moon and he puts the vial on that?

55:54.580 --> 55:54.940
Mining.

55:54.940 --> 55:57.640
He was implying things are being mined on the moon.

55:57.700 --> 55:57.840
So he.

55:57.900 --> 55:59.660
And so then Bryce looks at it.

55:59.660 --> 55:59.940
Right.

56:00.060 --> 56:00.380
And.

56:00.540 --> 56:01.440
I didn't shake it.

56:01.520 --> 56:07.260
So what I saw was just, you know, I less than half of it were these little flakes and

56:07.260 --> 56:11.020
I just looked at it and I have no experience with gold.

56:11.140 --> 56:11.760
I didn't know.

56:11.760 --> 56:16.600
But how do you go from like secrets around the nature of reality to like.

56:16.840 --> 56:17.260
I don't know.

56:17.340 --> 56:21.080
It actually deals with natural resources possibly derived from the.

56:21.220 --> 56:22.140
I don't know.

56:22.140 --> 56:26.120
Again, this is, and he was saying it in a way that was like not even casual.

56:26.120 --> 56:28.760
It was like, how could you not know this?

56:28.820 --> 56:31.500
It was, he had this like disdain for us.

56:31.500 --> 56:31.800
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

56:31.800 --> 56:34.640
Jesse, I have a theory though, because that is a great question.

56:34.800 --> 56:38.680
It's not like Brent and I have not spent a lot of time debating things like that.

56:38.680 --> 56:40.380
But here's a, here's a good example.

56:40.540 --> 56:44.300
What if his job was to find out how gullible the two of us were?

56:44.440 --> 56:44.600
Yeah.

56:44.600 --> 56:51.300
And so at some point he pulls out this thing to test us to see if we'll buy that hook line

56:51.300 --> 56:51.820
and sinker.

56:51.920 --> 56:56.260
And by the way, just to wrap, put a little wrap on, because you said, did you take the

56:56.260 --> 56:56.540
deal?

56:56.680 --> 56:59.220
Obviously, if we'd probably taken it, we wouldn't be on your show.

56:59.480 --> 57:00.140
Maybe we would.

57:00.180 --> 57:00.580
I don't know.

57:00.580 --> 57:07.700
But what happened was during that meeting, I don't know why I was just a pragmatic producer

57:07.700 --> 57:12.000
and I knew that there were people on our writing staff who depend on residuals, right?

57:12.020 --> 57:13.180
That's how they feed their family.

57:13.180 --> 57:18.540
So I started asking, I know this sounds ridiculous, but, you know, I was in my executive producer

57:18.540 --> 57:21.860
showrunner kind of mode and I'm like, so how would that work?

57:21.920 --> 57:27.960
You would give us ideas that you would want us to put in scripts and then who would get

57:27.960 --> 57:31.560
credit for, you know, about the writer's guild with the residuals and.

57:31.880 --> 57:33.900
So I'm, I'm talking writer's guild stuff.

57:34.360 --> 57:37.800
And actually I did have one very specific memory.

57:37.980 --> 57:43.000
One of the things that really set him off is he was saying in the second season,

57:43.000 --> 57:45.200
you need to do more stuff in the water.

57:45.920 --> 57:46.280
Okay.

57:46.480 --> 57:47.460
More stuff in the water.

57:47.460 --> 57:50.460
Cause Navy and USOs and all that.

57:50.740 --> 57:56.140
And I, I went into this riff about, uh, well, you know, water is very expensive.

57:56.140 --> 58:00.720
You got to get a tank and you got to shoot in the tank and you know, the, it takes forever

58:00.720 --> 58:03.380
in the studios and that just set him off.

58:03.380 --> 58:06.880
And then when I started asking about the writer's guild, he just got pissed off.

58:06.960 --> 58:07.840
The two of them left.

58:07.840 --> 58:10.200
And so we thought, okay, that's it.

58:10.300 --> 58:11.380
But it wasn't it.

58:11.440 --> 58:13.440
There was one final beat on this thing.

58:13.540 --> 58:16.680
And, and that was, again, time goes by.

58:16.780 --> 58:17.980
Brent gets another call.

58:18.200 --> 58:18.860
Brent was the conduit.

58:18.860 --> 58:19.400
I'm the weak link.

58:19.580 --> 58:21.440
I'm, I'm, I'm, I'm the one with the mark.

58:21.440 --> 58:26.340
Well, I still am wondering if that's John Harrington being like, give him another chance, you know,

58:26.340 --> 58:26.780
or something.

58:27.200 --> 58:28.880
It's a great, it's a great.

58:29.160 --> 58:31.860
Well, if this next beat was John Harrington, that's a little terrifying.

58:31.860 --> 58:32.320
It's weird.

58:32.380 --> 58:32.940
It's strange.

58:33.040 --> 58:37.160
So I guess the, the, the thing was Bryce seems a little difficult.

58:37.380 --> 58:39.020
I believe is what they were saying.

58:39.140 --> 58:43.180
You know, he seems like, you know, we're, we wouldn't ordinarily do this, but we do feel

58:43.180 --> 58:45.300
like maybe you should have one final chance.

58:45.300 --> 58:47.340
So that would fit with a Harrington.

58:47.340 --> 58:49.040
So they were trying to divide you guys essentially.

58:49.040 --> 58:51.500
Yeah, I think from their point of view, I was good cop.

58:51.540 --> 58:52.000
He was bad.

58:52.060 --> 58:52.380
Yeah.

58:52.440 --> 58:52.640
Right.

58:53.080 --> 58:53.400
So.

58:53.700 --> 58:54.480
Or foolish cop.

58:54.860 --> 58:55.840
I, I get this phone call.

58:55.940 --> 58:57.480
You know, my assistant comes in and goes, it's JC.

58:57.600 --> 58:59.380
I was like, I thought this was over with.

59:00.080 --> 59:04.620
And he said, listen, um, obviously that meeting did not go well.

59:05.040 --> 59:07.260
Um, we're going to give you one more chance.

59:07.600 --> 59:09.480
Um, here's what's going to happen.

59:10.240 --> 59:13.320
Um, I'm bringing in someone much higher this time.

59:13.880 --> 59:18.900
Um, it's an admiral and his boat is coming into.

59:19.620 --> 59:19.820
Sam.

59:19.900 --> 59:20.320
There were there.

59:20.440 --> 59:24.380
He said there was a ship in the long beach Harbor in the long beach Harbor and that they

59:24.380 --> 59:30.380
could not, uh, uh, check us into the ship because you can't have, you can't bring in

59:30.380 --> 59:35.180
a couple of Hollywood screenwriters onto a ship to meet an admiral, to talk about UFOs.

59:35.180 --> 59:36.380
That ain't going to work.

59:36.580 --> 59:36.980
Right.

59:36.980 --> 59:41.960
So I'm, I'm like listening to all of this and he said, so what's going to happen is

59:41.960 --> 59:47.680
he, he is going to come off of the ship with a cover story of visiting a deceased friend.

59:47.900 --> 59:50.700
We need you to meet at a cemetery at midnight.

59:51.080 --> 59:51.520
Right.

59:51.520 --> 59:54.500
That is, here's the, here's the name of the gravestone you're going to meet at.

59:54.600 --> 59:56.960
And all I heard was cemetery at midnight.

59:56.960 --> 01:00:00.880
I'm like, okay, here's, I'm, I'm a writer, but this is what I'm seeing.

01:00:01.220 --> 01:00:02.220
Bryce and I walk up.

01:00:02.600 --> 01:00:04.520
There is no name that we're looking for.

01:00:04.720 --> 01:00:07.440
There's our names on tombstones and two graves.

01:00:07.440 --> 01:00:11.640
And as we're processing that, we get capped from behind and that's where we're laid to rest.

01:00:11.640 --> 01:00:14.980
You have to understand the way this finally ultimately played out is Brent walks into

01:00:14.980 --> 01:00:18.820
my office and says, I just, uh, had another call with the JC.

01:00:18.820 --> 01:00:19.760
And I'm like, yeah.

01:00:19.880 --> 01:00:22.940
And he gets to cemetery at midnight, which I agree.

01:00:23.160 --> 01:00:23.740
I agree.

01:00:23.740 --> 01:00:24.460
It's insane.

01:00:24.620 --> 01:00:26.920
All we can do is bear witness to what happened.

01:00:27.040 --> 01:00:29.980
So again, we're not vouching that it seems reasonable.

01:00:29.980 --> 01:00:31.560
It seemed insane to us.

01:00:31.600 --> 01:00:36.600
And I said to Brent at the time, you know, I've got a wife and I got three kids and there

01:00:36.600 --> 01:00:40.520
is no way in hell I will be meeting anybody at a cemetery at midnight.

01:00:40.680 --> 01:00:43.760
And so we stopped calling them back.

01:00:44.300 --> 01:00:50.220
But, but we have in terms of doing this new show, had to think about what our mental state

01:00:50.220 --> 01:00:51.140
was at that point.

01:00:51.140 --> 01:00:54.660
And to be completely honest, Jesse, we talked about it.

01:00:54.840 --> 01:01:00.320
You know, we said, if this, if, if we were to push these guys for a higher standard of proof

01:01:00.320 --> 01:01:04.640
and they were able to prove who they were, would we take the deal anyway?

01:01:05.060 --> 01:01:06.120
What's the answer there?

01:01:06.120 --> 01:01:07.620
And the answer was, we just wouldn't.

01:01:07.620 --> 01:01:13.260
We just felt like we would cede the narrative, uh, thrust of our own show to people who we

01:01:13.260 --> 01:01:14.840
didn't know what they would demand of us.

01:01:14.940 --> 01:01:17.240
We didn't, we didn't feel good about them.

01:01:17.280 --> 01:01:21.500
I mean, the guy that we, we thought that the guy that came and was so abusive to us in the,

01:01:21.760 --> 01:01:23.940
in the conference room would be our boss.

01:01:23.940 --> 01:01:27.700
And we thought we already have studio bosses and network bosses.

01:01:27.880 --> 01:01:30.940
We don't need a boss from O&I, right?

01:01:30.940 --> 01:01:36.920
Do you guys think that any other directors in Hollywood have taken similar deals?

