01:10:41.020 --> 01:10:46.120
So we caved, we said, okay, well, if that's all we have to do.

01:10:46.260 --> 01:10:50.360
So we started shooting, you know, we, we, we did what they wanted.

01:10:50.440 --> 01:10:52.600
No more men in black in the suits.

01:10:52.720 --> 01:10:53.520
We started shooting.

01:10:53.880 --> 01:10:57.000
Do you think that was a Sony thing or a Spielberg Amblin thing?

01:10:57.000 --> 01:10:58.380
Well, it was conveyed to us.

01:10:58.480 --> 01:11:02.480
We never spoke to, like, look, we did not talk to Steven Spielberg or Barry Sonnenfeld.

01:11:02.680 --> 01:11:10.920
We had lawyers from Amblin talking to lawyers from Columbia TV, talking to executives from

01:11:10.920 --> 01:11:12.940
Columbia TV, talking to us.

01:11:13.040 --> 01:11:13.280
Okay.

01:11:13.280 --> 01:11:19.840
But so anything we're saying here, um, definitely came to us, you know, through lawyers and,

01:11:19.840 --> 01:11:22.020
and executives, but not directly.

01:11:22.020 --> 01:11:24.740
We never, you know, had that kind of situation.

01:11:25.280 --> 01:11:27.220
And we thought we'd taken care of it.

01:11:27.260 --> 01:11:30.140
We, we actually did a fine replace in our script.

01:11:30.140 --> 01:11:33.500
So everywhere we said men in black, we had to come up with a new name.

01:11:33.500 --> 01:11:36.540
It's not the best name, but it's only one out of thousands.

01:11:36.740 --> 01:11:38.580
Everybody went through, they could sign off on.

01:11:38.720 --> 01:11:39.820
We called them cloakers.

01:11:40.520 --> 01:11:40.800
Okay.

01:11:40.820 --> 01:11:45.900
So the cloakers dressed in green and blue and gray and brown.

01:11:45.900 --> 01:11:46.520
Right.

01:11:46.800 --> 01:11:49.300
And we thought we had dodged a bullet.

01:11:49.660 --> 01:11:50.020
Okay.

