01:55:27.680 --> 01:55:28.720
Twice you go, wow.

01:55:28.800 --> 01:55:30.180
Like that's weird.

01:55:30.340 --> 01:55:32.600
Three times you go, okay, it's you dude.

01:55:32.640 --> 01:55:34.320
Like you're a magnet for this stuff.

01:55:34.520 --> 01:55:35.640
Four, five, six.

01:55:35.820 --> 01:55:36.600
I'm going to leave the.

01:55:37.440 --> 01:55:38.940
But you're not a stranger anymore.

01:55:39.120 --> 01:55:40.420
So you did a really smart thing.

01:55:40.660 --> 01:55:40.780
Okay.

01:55:40.780 --> 01:55:41.180
Nice.

01:55:41.420 --> 01:55:41.680
Okay.

01:55:41.760 --> 01:55:41.980
Yeah.

01:55:41.980 --> 01:55:42.800
We're friends now.

01:55:42.800 --> 01:55:43.280
You're safe.

01:55:43.440 --> 01:55:43.860
You're safe.

01:55:43.980 --> 01:55:44.640
Well played.

01:55:44.720 --> 01:55:44.820
Yeah.

01:55:44.880 --> 01:55:45.060
Yeah.

01:55:46.200 --> 01:55:46.640
Wise.

01:55:47.060 --> 01:55:50.260
Uh, so, um, I'm not going to get into all of them.

01:55:50.280 --> 01:55:52.000
Um, but I, there's a couple I want to highlight.

01:55:52.120 --> 01:55:54.160
The first one happened to me when I was five years old.

01:55:54.700 --> 01:55:56.800
Um, I was living in Berkeley at the time.

01:55:57.080 --> 01:56:01.880
Um, it was before we moved to Walnut Creek and there's, uh, the Berkeley Hills has this

01:56:01.880 --> 01:56:03.640
park at the top called Tilden park.

01:56:04.120 --> 01:56:08.940
And, uh, there's a road called Marin Boulevard or Avenue or something, which kind of comes

01:56:08.940 --> 01:56:13.280
down the side of the Berkeley Hills in a road that just kind of does this.

01:56:13.280 --> 01:56:14.160
It's like a roller coaster.

01:56:14.320 --> 01:56:18.420
And I had been up there with my dad and we were in an old VW bug.

01:56:18.720 --> 01:56:22.220
And I used to love coming down that road cause it was like steep.

01:56:22.220 --> 01:56:22.540
Right.

01:56:22.580 --> 01:56:27.960
And then, so I would, I was sitting there holding on to kind of the, the, the bar in front of

01:56:27.960 --> 01:56:31.640
the, the glove box, riding the car down.

01:56:31.640 --> 01:56:31.920
Right.

01:56:31.920 --> 01:56:36.420
And we're kind of going down and, and I noticed kind of the corner of my eye that there's

01:56:36.420 --> 01:56:41.280
someone's washing their car, uh, and the water is kind of running off and it's, and

01:56:41.280 --> 01:56:44.180
I'm thinking, oh, we're chasing the water as it's going down the hill.

01:56:44.180 --> 01:56:45.500
And I'm thinking, oh, this is so cool.

01:56:45.960 --> 01:56:50.800
And in front of us, which I'm not really paying attention to, there's a girl on a motorcycle.

01:56:51.100 --> 01:56:54.520
She's in like jean shorts and a halter top, no helmet.

01:56:54.520 --> 01:57:02.820
Since it's, this was 68 and I'm watching her and watching the water and she turns.

01:57:03.440 --> 01:57:08.100
And as she's turning, the water has just gone across the street that she's turning into.

01:57:08.100 --> 01:57:13.820
And when the back tire hits that water, her bike slides, stops, flips her.

01:57:14.020 --> 01:57:19.220
She goes flipping over and hits, they used to have metal fenders in those days, hits the

01:57:19.220 --> 01:57:21.520
metal fender, knocks her head right off.

01:57:21.720 --> 01:57:27.040
It rolls into the road and my dad has to slam on the brakes to not hit her head.

01:57:27.880 --> 01:57:28.460
Oh dude.

01:57:29.080 --> 01:57:31.880
So, and I'm watching all of this, right?

01:57:31.920 --> 01:57:32.220
Oh.

01:57:32.220 --> 01:57:36.940
Hang in on and my dad turns my head and says, don't look, right?

01:57:36.960 --> 01:57:39.020
And he gets out of the car to go deal with this.

01:57:39.320 --> 01:57:40.520
Well, of course my head's on a swivel.

01:57:40.700 --> 01:57:43.760
That's all I can do is look, but I'm five years old.

01:57:43.860 --> 01:57:48.980
So in my mind, I'm thinking, okay, well, I'm not, I'm not focusing on the fact that the

01:57:48.980 --> 01:57:52.000
body is just flailing and blood everywhere and whatnot.

01:57:52.000 --> 01:57:55.660
I'm focusing on the head thinking, oh, well, they can just put the head back on like you

01:57:55.660 --> 01:57:57.680
would like a GI Joe doll or something, right?

01:57:57.800 --> 01:58:01.280
It didn't really occur to me, but that happened, right?

01:58:01.280 --> 01:58:03.040
So that's the first death that I saw.

01:58:03.420 --> 01:58:08.200
The second death that I saw was, well, actually, this is the third death.

01:58:08.260 --> 01:58:11.940
I can't talk about the second one because it's, my mom will get upset.

01:58:12.140 --> 01:58:16.000
The third death was, I was on Telegraph Avenue.

01:58:16.700 --> 01:58:23.100
I'm 15 years old, 16 years old, and I've got a girlfriend or I've gotten a date.

01:58:23.160 --> 01:58:23.460
I'm sorry.

01:58:24.000 --> 01:58:24.960
We're walking down.

01:58:25.060 --> 01:58:27.700
It's a Sunday and it's like twilight.

01:58:27.700 --> 01:58:31.620
It's like just perfect because all of the day markets are gone and whatnot.

01:58:31.760 --> 01:58:34.880
So everyone's moved out and it's just kind of like quiet Telegraph Avenue.

01:58:35.840 --> 01:58:39.580
And we are heading to one of the restaurants that we know will not cart us.

01:58:39.800 --> 01:58:41.260
So we're going to go have pizza and beer.

01:58:41.500 --> 01:58:45.180
So we're walking, you know, talking and our hands kind of hit and all of a sudden we're

01:58:45.180 --> 01:58:47.900
holding hands like, oh my goodness.

01:58:47.900 --> 01:58:48.580
That's the moment.

01:58:48.680 --> 01:58:49.500
Like this is the moment.

01:58:49.560 --> 01:58:50.900
Like everything is perfect.

01:58:50.900 --> 01:58:56.200
But a couple seconds after that, there's a weird rush of motion and I'm like, what's

01:58:56.200 --> 01:58:56.660
going on?

01:58:56.700 --> 01:59:01.880
And the next thing I know, my arm is, you know, yanked backwards as the girl is running

01:59:01.880 --> 01:59:03.040
the opposite direction.

01:59:03.820 --> 01:59:06.580
And I kind of let her go and she just sprints.

01:59:06.700 --> 01:59:08.000
She's sprinting the opposite direction.

01:59:08.080 --> 01:59:09.780
I'm like, wait, what's going on?

01:59:10.280 --> 01:59:15.840
And I kind of looked down and there had been like a weird noise that I, my brain couldn't

01:59:15.840 --> 01:59:16.600
quite process.

01:59:16.600 --> 01:59:20.340
And I looked down and there's a body this far in front of us.

01:59:20.740 --> 01:59:28.940
And it's somebody who obviously has landed on their head and their head is crushed open

01:59:28.940 --> 01:59:34.740
and their pants are down around their ankles and they're just flailing and all sorts of

01:59:34.740 --> 01:59:35.400
stuff is happening.

01:59:35.580 --> 01:59:36.220
Because they've jumped.

01:59:36.620 --> 01:59:41.200
Because when I look up three stories up, there's an open window with a curtain blowing and they

01:59:41.200 --> 01:59:41.500
jumped.

01:59:42.000 --> 01:59:42.800
They missed us.

01:59:42.800 --> 01:59:45.860
They missed landing on my head and her head by this much.

01:59:45.860 --> 01:59:47.100
Oh my God.

01:59:47.540 --> 01:59:52.400
And so again, like, what are the odds that this would happen?

01:59:52.760 --> 01:59:55.700
So I, I don't even know how to respond.

01:59:55.760 --> 01:59:56.680
I'm just kind of numb.

01:59:56.900 --> 02:00:00.420
And I think, okay, I've got to, there's, and no one is stopping by the way.

02:00:00.420 --> 02:00:03.420
There's like a skateboarder that runs by or drives by and goes, oh, gnarly.

02:00:03.480 --> 02:00:04.900
Like, and it's like very surreal.

02:00:05.320 --> 02:00:08.120
And so I walk into the hotel, this turns out to be a hotel.

02:00:08.520 --> 02:00:11.900
And there's a guy on the phone, you know, talking to somebody behind the counter and he's

02:00:11.900 --> 02:00:12.880
like, oh yeah, I'm doing this stuff.

02:00:12.880 --> 02:00:15.000
And I, and he, he's irritated that I'm there.

02:00:15.100 --> 02:00:16.060
I'm like, he's like, yes, what?

02:00:16.160 --> 02:00:19.520
And I go, some guy's dying out on your sidewalk.

02:00:20.260 --> 02:00:20.620
Okay.

02:00:21.160 --> 02:00:23.200
I'm like, he jumped from your window.

02:00:23.500 --> 02:00:24.700
Well, how many stories up?

02:00:24.740 --> 02:00:26.560
I'm like, I don't know, three or four.

02:00:26.700 --> 02:00:27.660
What'd he look like?

02:00:28.640 --> 02:00:31.500
I go, I, he can't really see his face anymore.

02:00:31.560 --> 02:00:32.220
Did he have a beard?

02:00:32.860 --> 02:00:33.800
I think so.

02:00:33.880 --> 02:00:34.620
Hold on a second.

02:00:34.900 --> 02:00:35.100
Yeah.

02:00:35.220 --> 02:00:35.600
Guess what?

02:00:35.700 --> 02:00:36.460
Jim jumped again.

02:00:36.840 --> 02:00:37.340
Yeah, I know.

02:00:37.340 --> 02:00:38.940
And why does this happen on my shift?

02:00:39.120 --> 02:00:40.040
I'll call the police.

02:00:40.100 --> 02:00:40.520
Thank you.

02:00:41.320 --> 02:00:41.720
What?

02:00:42.280 --> 02:00:46.680
And I'm like, so just go back out there.

02:00:46.680 --> 02:00:48.700
He's like, he's like back to his conversation.

02:00:48.900 --> 02:00:50.080
So I walked back out there.

02:00:50.160 --> 02:00:53.620
There's still, no one has stopped and the body has stopped moving.

02:00:53.880 --> 02:00:54.280
Right.

02:00:54.840 --> 02:00:55.240
Okay.

02:00:55.400 --> 02:00:56.520
I'm not going to dwell on it.

02:00:56.580 --> 02:00:59.740
The whole point is, is that very strange, very surreal.

02:00:59.880 --> 02:01:00.720
What are the odds?

02:01:01.240 --> 02:01:02.900
Seven of these?

02:01:03.020 --> 02:01:03.360
Six.

02:01:03.500 --> 02:01:04.280
Six of these?

02:01:04.280 --> 02:01:04.940
That was two.

02:01:05.660 --> 02:01:06.060
Okay.

02:01:06.820 --> 02:01:10.460
One of them had a really weird component that I want to bring up because it's important

02:01:10.460 --> 02:01:11.340
to Disclosure Day.

02:01:11.960 --> 02:01:18.060
One of them, I was at LAX and it was early, it was between kind of like right after college

02:01:18.060 --> 02:01:19.960
before I like my career really took off.

02:01:20.840 --> 02:01:26.300
I'm working as a limousine driver in Hollywood, which is a job I would recommend to no one,

02:01:26.420 --> 02:01:27.240
by the way.

02:01:27.240 --> 02:01:34.220
And, um, I'm coming out of LAX, uh, and I've just dropped off someone and walked them to

02:01:34.220 --> 02:01:35.240
their gate with their bags.

02:01:35.240 --> 02:01:39.620
And I'm walking over to my, to the town car, whatever that I've got parked in the parking

02:01:39.620 --> 02:01:39.840
lot.

02:01:40.000 --> 02:01:42.400
And LAX is like two big bands.

02:01:42.400 --> 02:01:46.420
Like, you know, it's like there's the inner thing where like shuttles and whatnot come

02:01:46.420 --> 02:01:49.880
and then there's like the big loop that you can just drive around with cars and buses

02:01:49.880 --> 02:01:50.860
and all sorts of other stuff.

02:01:50.860 --> 02:01:58.820
And I'm walking across the middle, the inside band, and I'm looking straight across to people

02:01:58.820 --> 02:01:59.840
that are waiting over here.

02:01:59.900 --> 02:02:05.200
And there's a bus parked right at the edge of the, the crosswalk.

02:02:05.640 --> 02:02:09.380
So you can't see the traffic, you know, moving back and forth.

02:02:09.600 --> 02:02:14.520
And meanwhile, I'm walking, as I'm walking to the crosswalk, it's red.

02:02:14.800 --> 02:02:15.320
Okay.

02:02:15.360 --> 02:02:17.640
So, um, everything has stopped.

02:02:18.100 --> 02:02:19.500
Um, I'm sorry, it's green.

02:02:19.500 --> 02:02:24.140
So everybody's walking across it and the woman next to me catches up to me and she

02:02:24.140 --> 02:02:29.780
is, uh, an airline stewardess and she's arguing with a passenger who's followed her out there.

02:02:29.780 --> 02:02:32.840
And she's like, you know, kind of pissed off and arguing with him.

02:02:32.940 --> 02:02:34.960
And this is all happening in parallel to me.

02:02:35.060 --> 02:02:42.080
And so we step onto the little medium between the two through lanes and I noticed, oh wait,

02:02:42.200 --> 02:02:43.720
the light has just turned red.

02:02:44.500 --> 02:02:44.980
Okay.

02:02:45.280 --> 02:02:47.260
But there's a bus right here.

02:02:47.260 --> 02:02:51.040
So I stop, but she's arguing with the guy.

02:02:51.160 --> 02:02:52.500
So she's not paying attention.

02:02:52.620 --> 02:02:54.460
The last thing she saw was that it was green.

02:02:54.920 --> 02:02:59.700
So she walks out and I'm kind of like, everything goes into slow motion.

02:02:59.700 --> 02:03:05.120
And I'm like, oh no, like she's walking out and all of a sudden somebody comes that

02:03:05.120 --> 02:03:06.480
she doesn't see and hits her.

02:03:06.480 --> 02:03:10.560
And her whole body goes flying up into the air.

02:03:11.220 --> 02:03:14.260
And here's the interesting thing about this.

02:03:14.440 --> 02:03:18.920
In that moment, I, LAX is a very noisy place.

02:03:19.440 --> 02:03:22.340
I heard nothing except her breathing.

02:03:23.120 --> 02:03:23.600
What?

02:03:23.600 --> 02:03:26.520
She is flying up in the air.

02:03:26.960 --> 02:03:29.420
All of the sounds disappear.

02:03:29.660 --> 02:03:35.360
And all I'm hearing is, and I'm like, what is that noise?

02:03:35.460 --> 02:03:38.640
And then she comes down and she slams onto the ground.

02:03:39.000 --> 02:03:42.980
She kind of is all, her body's all tangled up and stuff.

02:03:43.100 --> 02:03:46.860
She kind of looks up through her hair is in her face and her face is all bloody.

02:03:46.860 --> 02:03:51.620
And she gasps and then just dies right in that moment.

02:03:51.800 --> 02:03:53.920
All of the noise came back in LAX.

02:03:54.060 --> 02:03:57.320
So I had this like incredible, weird connection.

02:03:57.320 --> 02:03:59.860
We're kind of time slowed and audio manipulated.

02:03:59.860 --> 02:04:03.840
And I was suddenly connected to her in some weird way.

02:04:04.040 --> 02:04:04.520
Right.

02:04:04.800 --> 02:04:05.280
Okay.

02:04:05.620 --> 02:04:09.560
So last one I'll tell you about, we're at the dark skies production office.

02:04:09.560 --> 02:04:10.280
It's late night.

02:04:10.380 --> 02:04:11.180
We're working one night.

02:04:11.240 --> 02:04:14.900
Everyone's doing stuff and it's like on a Friday night.

02:04:14.900 --> 02:04:20.420
Um, and all of a sudden there's like an explosion outside on the, and it's like in the worst

02:04:20.420 --> 02:04:22.580
part of North Hollywood, it's a kind of industrial area.

02:04:22.880 --> 02:04:24.180
There's an explosion outside.

02:04:24.180 --> 02:04:26.840
So, um, my assistant and I go running out.

02:04:26.900 --> 02:04:32.640
We're the first ones outside and we see across the street, there's a car that has like flipped

02:04:32.640 --> 02:04:35.040
and gone into an old like auto yard.

02:04:35.040 --> 02:04:39.700
And it's behind like a, it's flipped and it's gone behind a barbed wire fence.

02:04:39.700 --> 02:04:42.120
So there's like no way we can get to that.

02:04:42.120 --> 02:04:46.300
And then down the street, there's another car that's gone off the road into kind of

02:04:46.300 --> 02:04:47.160
the parking lot.

02:04:47.260 --> 02:04:49.360
And it's kind of like stopped.

02:04:49.980 --> 02:04:55.140
And I looked down there and the front door opens and a teenage kid runs out, just takes

02:04:55.140 --> 02:04:57.480
off, like hit and run, whatever was going on there.

02:04:57.800 --> 02:05:00.020
So I look at my assistant and I go, go call 9-1-1.

02:05:00.160 --> 02:05:01.520
So I run down to the car.

02:05:03.520 --> 02:05:04.500
You get down to the car.

02:05:04.660 --> 02:05:05.900
Well, obviously the driver's gone.

02:05:05.900 --> 02:05:10.640
So I go over to the passenger seat and I start to look in the window and there's an

02:05:10.640 --> 02:05:14.360
older, like Hispanic man, just kind of slumped in the seat.

02:05:14.660 --> 02:05:18.060
And I like knock and I'm like, sir, sir, are you okay?

02:05:18.320 --> 02:05:19.680
Does not have a seatbelt on.

02:05:19.820 --> 02:05:22.920
He kind of looks up at me like this and there's blood coming out of his ear.

02:05:23.900 --> 02:05:27.640
And I, I kind of reach in and the door's unlocked.

02:05:27.760 --> 02:05:30.660
So I open it up and I kneel down and I go, sir, are you okay?

02:05:30.760 --> 02:05:31.900
We're calling 9-1-1.

02:05:31.900 --> 02:05:33.020
There's going to be help here soon.

02:05:33.100 --> 02:05:39.340
And he reaches out this hand like this and I take it and he's looking at me and he's

02:05:39.340 --> 02:05:40.780
kind of like breathing really slow.

02:05:41.080 --> 02:05:48.820
And all of a sudden he goes, and in that moment, I feel all of his energy go through my body.

02:05:49.260 --> 02:05:52.380
Like his soul, like that's the only way I can describe it.

02:05:52.560 --> 02:05:55.380
And I'm seeing images of his life.

02:05:55.720 --> 02:05:59.120
You know, it's like the life, when you say like people see their life flash before your

02:05:59.120 --> 02:06:01.260
eyes, his life flashed before my eyes.

02:06:01.260 --> 02:06:05.720
I'm hearing Spanish and all these things that I, they're not in my consciousness.

02:06:07.180 --> 02:06:09.440
And all of a sudden he's gone.

02:06:09.560 --> 02:06:10.100
He's dead.

02:06:10.260 --> 02:06:11.020
Oh my God.

02:06:11.040 --> 02:06:11.660
In that moment.

02:06:11.660 --> 02:06:17.000
And there's this pause and I'm like, wow, suddenly all of these incidents kept moving

02:06:17.000 --> 02:06:19.720
me closer and closer to an understanding of death.

02:06:20.000 --> 02:06:22.660
And now I get this experience, right?

02:06:22.660 --> 02:06:28.460
And in the back seat, I hear Papa and this little boy pops up.

02:06:28.620 --> 02:06:33.140
He knew somehow intuitively because nothing was said really for a minute or so between

02:06:33.140 --> 02:06:35.580
he just knew that his father had passed away.

02:06:35.580 --> 02:06:35.960
Right.

02:06:36.520 --> 02:06:38.560
So all of that happens.

02:06:38.800 --> 02:06:42.860
And then when you say, well, why would all of that happen to me?

02:06:42.860 --> 02:06:45.060
Like we say, well, that's a curse, right?

02:06:45.960 --> 02:06:47.100
But here's the thing.

02:06:47.780 --> 02:06:51.860
About five years ago, I had cancer and I, I'm not going to go through that whole journey,

02:06:51.960 --> 02:06:52.720
but I almost died.

02:06:52.860 --> 02:06:54.660
I was in a hospital during COVID.

02:06:55.160 --> 02:06:57.900
I had had a whole reaction to something.

02:06:57.960 --> 02:07:01.180
I got sepsis from after the cancer surgery and whatnot.

02:07:01.320 --> 02:07:02.000
Oh Jesus, man.

02:07:02.000 --> 02:07:08.800
So I'm in a hospital all by myself in ICU during COVID with a temperature of 105.5.

02:07:08.840 --> 02:07:09.600
Oh my God.

02:07:09.740 --> 02:07:12.200
And for several days, I'm just battling that, right?

02:07:12.240 --> 02:07:15.660
And the nurses are like, they keep making me sign the thing because I have a purple wristband

02:07:15.660 --> 02:07:17.620
on, like, you don't want to be revived.

02:07:17.780 --> 02:07:18.540
We're just confirming.

02:07:18.660 --> 02:07:21.480
We're just confirming because you're not going to probably make it.

02:07:22.160 --> 02:07:26.980
And at one point in one of those nights, I'm just laying there by myself and all of

02:07:26.980 --> 02:07:30.860
a sudden light entities come to the foot of my bed.

02:07:32.060 --> 02:07:37.480
And because of everything that had happened to me in my life, I wasn't scared of death.

02:07:38.580 --> 02:07:39.680
I was there.

02:07:39.920 --> 02:07:42.080
I understood it intuitively.

02:07:42.080 --> 02:07:46.440
I just was like, oh, this is my time if I want it.

02:07:48.260 --> 02:07:52.100
And I, I didn't, it wasn't like, oh, hey, it's grandpa Joe.

02:07:52.320 --> 02:07:53.060
It's dad.

02:07:53.180 --> 02:07:53.940
It's grandma, whatever.

02:07:54.020 --> 02:07:55.000
It was just weird.

02:07:55.000 --> 02:07:58.620
It was like that, this is why I respond to contacts a while.

02:07:58.680 --> 02:08:03.540
It was like the end of contact when Jodie Foster sees that light being kind of come closer

02:08:03.540 --> 02:08:04.960
and then it becomes her father.

02:08:05.580 --> 02:08:09.120
This was before it becomes, it was just that light, it was these light beings.

02:08:09.220 --> 02:08:13.160
There was three of them and they're just kind of there for me if I want them.

02:08:13.640 --> 02:08:15.440
And I don't speak to them.

02:08:15.520 --> 02:08:18.880
They don't speak to me, but I feel this real sense of calm.

02:08:19.380 --> 02:08:24.760
All of the body horror I was going through with a temperature of 105, I didn't feel anything.

02:08:24.760 --> 02:08:25.660
I just felt good.

02:08:26.020 --> 02:08:27.560
I felt like totally at peace.

02:08:27.860 --> 02:08:31.120
And I was like, no, I have something I still need to do.

02:08:31.200 --> 02:08:37.140
I didn't even know what it was at that time, but I just made that thought in my head and

02:08:37.140 --> 02:08:38.200
they just receded.

02:08:39.280 --> 02:08:39.380
Wow.

02:08:39.480 --> 02:08:40.340
And you got better.

02:08:40.640 --> 02:08:42.000
And I got better and here I am.

02:08:42.380 --> 02:08:43.100
That's amazing.

02:08:43.100 --> 02:08:47.140
And I, one of the things that I, you know, you can call this whatever you want, rationalization

02:08:47.140 --> 02:08:49.360
or writing your own narrative.

02:08:49.360 --> 02:08:52.920
When Bryce said, we need to do this podcast and you need to tell some of your stories.

02:08:52.920 --> 02:08:54.460
I'm like, you know what?

02:08:54.520 --> 02:08:58.140
This is what I was supposed, this is why I wanted to stay alive.

02:08:59.060 --> 02:09:03.260
And to, to, and when I went to my family, they said, they had been the ones that said,

02:09:03.360 --> 02:09:04.340
please don't tell these stories.

02:09:04.400 --> 02:09:06.420
Like this is, they were like, you know what?

02:09:06.480 --> 02:09:12.020
You need to tell these stories because if you had died when this happened, we would be

02:09:12.020 --> 02:09:13.480
telling your story secondhand.

02:09:13.480 --> 02:09:16.600
And that's not nearly as powerful as people hearing them from you.

02:09:17.240 --> 02:09:18.480
It all makes sense in hindsight.

02:09:18.860 --> 02:09:20.000
It all makes sense in hindsight.

02:09:20.660 --> 02:09:22.920
What do you think those light beings were?

02:09:22.920 --> 02:09:33.560
Um, I don't, it's hard for me to articulate this because I'm not a religious person and

02:09:33.560 --> 02:09:40.680
I, I will willingly admit that I resist trying to codify anything in religious terms, but

02:09:40.680 --> 02:09:46.120
I feel like in some ways, these were my guardian angel type beings.

02:09:46.460 --> 02:09:52.900
I felt a total like connection with them, not in a familial way, but

02:09:52.900 --> 02:09:55.620
just in a, in a coherence.

02:09:55.700 --> 02:09:59.640
There was like, I just, I just knew who they were and I trusted them and I felt like everything

02:09:59.640 --> 02:10:00.580
was going to be okay.

02:10:01.320 --> 02:10:05.960
So, and I felt like they had a connection with me, even though I didn't understand what

02:10:05.960 --> 02:10:06.320
it was.

02:10:06.320 --> 02:10:09.100
Did you get better right after that experience?

02:10:09.280 --> 02:10:12.560
I got better within the next 24 hours and I was leaving the hospital.

02:10:12.920 --> 02:10:13.320
Whoa.

02:10:13.760 --> 02:10:13.980
Yeah.

02:10:15.380 --> 02:10:15.820
Yeah.

02:10:16.180 --> 02:10:19.600
This, I don't even know what to say after all of that.

02:10:19.600 --> 02:10:23.100
I mean, that's a, those are some gnarly experiences.

02:10:23.100 --> 02:10:25.700
The six deaths that you witnessed.

02:10:25.700 --> 02:10:28.740
I don't, I mean, that's hard to hear for anyone.

02:10:28.740 --> 02:10:31.340
It's, it's super graphic and intense.

02:10:31.340 --> 02:10:36.600
And I can only imagine like, how are you, you're, you're able to tell the stories in

02:10:36.600 --> 02:10:37.580
such detail.

02:10:37.580 --> 02:10:45.100
And, uh, I imagine you had to, in each time sort of process and integrate what had just

02:10:45.100 --> 02:10:45.400
happened.

02:10:45.580 --> 02:10:45.600
Yes.

02:10:45.600 --> 02:10:47.580
But all of them are building on, right?

02:10:47.600 --> 02:10:51.540
So it's like you have the first experience when I'm five, I can barely comprehend it.

02:10:51.540 --> 02:10:51.780
Right.

02:10:51.800 --> 02:10:52.100
Right.

02:10:52.180 --> 02:10:54.560
And then experiences continue to build on that.

02:10:54.620 --> 02:10:58.880
And there, I wouldn't say, you know, there's a way to say, oh, you were being desensitized.

02:10:59.020 --> 02:11:01.100
No, I think I was being slowly awakened.

02:11:01.460 --> 02:11:01.860
Hmm.

02:11:01.920 --> 02:11:02.160
Right.

02:11:02.700 --> 02:11:05.740
And again, this is all like how you choose to view your own narrative.

02:11:05.740 --> 02:11:11.540
I could have viewed all of that as I'm, I'm traumatized.

02:11:11.660 --> 02:11:13.440
I need therapy for the rest of my life.

02:11:13.520 --> 02:11:15.560
I can't be around things that trigger me.

02:11:15.640 --> 02:11:20.060
I think that's one viable path you can take if you have those types of experiences.

02:11:20.640 --> 02:11:25.960
Fortunately, I don't know that I ever made a conscious choice to say, no, don't do that.

02:11:26.040 --> 02:11:32.000
Don't fall into that path, you know, but it, it, you know, now to connect a few other

02:11:32.000 --> 02:11:34.140
dots, you know, I've had out of body experiences.

02:11:34.140 --> 02:11:43.500
I have been visited by entities, not UFO, not like aliens, but like paranormal type entities.

02:11:43.720 --> 02:11:44.040
Like what?

02:11:45.620 --> 02:11:47.740
So here's one I'll share with you.

02:11:47.820 --> 02:11:49.880
I was in LA working.

02:11:50.060 --> 02:11:52.000
This is when my writing career was taking off.

02:11:52.000 --> 02:11:58.120
And, um, I was writing a script on, uh, a ghost story.

02:11:59.200 --> 02:12:03.980
And this, this is one of those things where you start to realize intention and like what

02:12:03.980 --> 02:12:08.340
you put your mind on, especially if you have a certain type of mind, you become a magnet

02:12:08.340 --> 02:12:09.020
for things.

02:12:09.300 --> 02:12:10.780
That's the only way to view this.

02:12:10.780 --> 02:12:18.000
I am trying to write the story and I get obsessed with this idea that I'm writing a comedy and

02:12:18.000 --> 02:12:23.280
I can't get past the scene where the main character sees his dead girlfriend as a ghost

02:12:23.280 --> 02:12:27.240
because I'm like, okay, all I can do right is the comedy version of that, but I need to

02:12:27.240 --> 02:12:28.220
know what would really happen.

02:12:28.320 --> 02:12:31.300
Like if I really saw a ghost, what's that reaction?

02:12:31.300 --> 02:12:34.560
And then I'll twist it and make it funny, but I need to know what would really happen.

02:12:34.560 --> 02:12:39.540
And so I, I'm like, I start reading some ghost stories and I'm like, well, this is all just

02:12:39.540 --> 02:12:41.740
very, it's not interesting.

02:12:41.740 --> 02:12:43.640
So it's like, I didn't find what I wanted.

02:12:43.840 --> 02:12:47.980
So I was going through this phase where I was very frustrated because I couldn't, I

02:12:47.980 --> 02:12:50.100
couldn't get the answers I wanted.

02:12:50.360 --> 02:12:55.760
And my ritual at that time was I would write, you know, uh, very late at night from probably

02:12:55.760 --> 02:12:57.360
about midnight till 4 a.m.

02:12:57.360 --> 02:12:59.840
And then I would sleep in, get up around noon.

02:12:59.960 --> 02:13:01.240
It's the writer's life, right?

02:13:01.240 --> 02:13:06.240
So I would get up and then I would walk out.

02:13:06.340 --> 02:13:07.440
I'd pick up the LA times.

02:13:07.540 --> 02:13:08.100
I'd come back.

02:13:08.160 --> 02:13:08.960
I'd sit in my bed.

02:13:09.020 --> 02:13:13.120
I'd read the bed, you know, the paper, whatever, start to plan out my day and I'd go do my

02:13:13.120 --> 02:13:13.380
thing.

02:13:14.300 --> 02:13:18.980
So I'm doing this one morning and my cat's on my leg.

02:13:19.040 --> 02:13:19.900
I'm sitting on the bed.

02:13:19.960 --> 02:13:20.240
It's broad.

02:13:20.320 --> 02:13:25.740
I mean, it's like noon and I'm reading the LA times and already my mind is drifting to,

02:13:25.740 --> 02:13:28.920
am I going to even try and write that scene again today?

02:13:29.040 --> 02:13:29.360
Right.

02:13:29.360 --> 02:13:32.740
And I hear this voice say, I'm right here.

02:13:35.300 --> 02:13:37.960
I'm like, I mean, here's the thing.

02:13:38.600 --> 02:13:41.680
A voice has spoken to me a number of times throughout my life.

02:13:42.140 --> 02:13:47.280
The way, the best way I can describe it is, and it does, it's weird is that it's if someone's

02:13:47.280 --> 02:13:52.900
putting like one of those like cooking funnels in my right ear and they're giving me, there's

02:13:52.900 --> 02:13:54.300
pouring in pure information.

02:13:54.300 --> 02:13:55.480
It's not words.

02:13:55.480 --> 02:13:59.020
It's just like intelligence, pure intelligence.

02:13:59.020 --> 02:14:00.160
And I just know it.

02:14:00.160 --> 02:14:04.000
And it's not male or female, but it's like, it's an order.

02:14:04.080 --> 02:14:08.180
It's like, oh, I feel like that moment I'm a Manchurian candidate and something is speaking

02:14:08.180 --> 02:14:09.340
to me in a higher language.

02:14:09.700 --> 02:14:11.140
And I just understand it.

02:14:11.140 --> 02:14:12.400
And it's like, I'm right here.

02:14:13.380 --> 02:14:14.240
Where is here?

02:14:14.240 --> 02:14:14.700
I don't.

02:14:14.800 --> 02:14:19.080
So I lower the paper and there's a woman standing at the foot of my bed.

02:14:19.780 --> 02:14:20.220
What?

02:14:21.280 --> 02:14:23.500
And not great.

02:14:23.500 --> 02:14:27.940
Um, but she's translucent, but three-dimensional.

02:14:28.660 --> 02:14:34.340
So I can see her full body and, but I can also see through her and she's in like kind

02:14:34.340 --> 02:14:42.540
of a tattered sundress and she's got long stringy blonde hair, but it's her eyes that

02:14:42.540 --> 02:14:43.040
get me.

02:14:43.040 --> 02:14:48.120
Her eyes are, imagine you give like a three-year-old a piece of charcoal and you say, draw a circle

02:14:48.120 --> 02:14:56.120
and they go, her eyes are two black circles that are undulating, which is not comforting.

02:14:56.660 --> 02:15:00.720
Like that woman's like, it's really bad one night stand.

02:15:01.840 --> 02:15:07.580
So I'm, I'm looking at this woman kind of like spellbound and all of a sudden there's

02:15:07.580 --> 02:15:08.680
like a rush of motion.

02:15:08.860 --> 02:15:10.420
The paper falls out of my hand.

02:15:10.520 --> 02:15:14.220
My cat digs into my legs, jumps off the bed, takes off.

02:15:14.500 --> 02:15:16.280
My head slams back.

02:15:16.280 --> 02:15:21.280
I'm, I'm, I hit the headboard and I feel my whole body being pushed down and like pain

02:15:21.280 --> 02:15:22.120
on my biceps.

02:15:22.120 --> 02:15:29.820
And I'm like, what the, and all of a sudden I'm stuck and I feel tingling around my neck

02:15:29.820 --> 02:15:32.380
and, and I kind of do this rack focus moment.

02:15:32.860 --> 02:15:35.160
She's jumped on top of me.

02:15:35.220 --> 02:15:36.660
She's pounced on me.

02:15:36.820 --> 02:15:43.540
Her knees are on my biceps and she's holding my arms down and she's holding right over me.

02:15:43.640 --> 02:15:45.100
Her hair is tickling me.

02:15:45.100 --> 02:15:51.800
Uh, and as I kind of take all of this in, I look up into her swirling black eyes and

02:15:51.800 --> 02:15:56.940
I see the most beautiful constellations and cosmos you've ever seen in your life.

02:15:57.020 --> 02:15:57.340
What?

02:15:57.540 --> 02:15:58.800
Like through her?

02:15:58.920 --> 02:16:03.140
Through her, like shots of NASA that NASA has of deep space through her eyes.

02:16:03.140 --> 02:16:08.500
And I have, at that point in my life, I've already had at least one out of body experience.

02:16:08.700 --> 02:16:15.720
I start to feel my soul leave my body going up into those eyes.

02:16:16.340 --> 02:16:19.460
I'm, I'm literally being pulled up like a vacuum.

02:16:20.140 --> 02:16:21.880
And then I hear that voice again.

02:16:21.880 --> 02:16:24.960
And the voice says, just look away.

02:16:26.640 --> 02:16:27.960
And again, it's a command.

02:16:27.960 --> 02:16:33.420
It's like, I, then I must just look away with all the strength I can muster.

02:16:33.420 --> 02:16:37.500
I turn until I'm not looking at the eyes and it's gone.

02:16:37.500 --> 02:16:39.960
And you know what my first reaction was?

02:16:40.700 --> 02:16:41.660
Come back.

02:16:43.260 --> 02:16:49.060
The reason was, is because I have never felt so alive in my life.

02:16:49.160 --> 02:16:54.580
I felt like if you just took two fingers and put them into an electrical socket, you're supercharged.

02:16:54.820 --> 02:16:56.280
I was looking around the room.

02:16:56.540 --> 02:16:59.780
I could look at the stucco and like, was like looking into the Grand Canyon.

02:16:59.960 --> 02:17:01.200
I could see every detail.

02:17:01.360 --> 02:17:05.200
Every dust particle was like a, you know, a sagebrush.

02:17:05.360 --> 02:17:05.460
Brilliant.

02:17:05.620 --> 02:17:06.780
I mean, it was incredible.

02:17:07.280 --> 02:17:10.500
And I, I wanted that experience to come back.

02:17:11.480 --> 02:17:12.580
And, but it didn't.

02:17:13.320 --> 02:17:14.240
I get on the phone.

02:17:14.440 --> 02:17:15.360
I call every friend.

02:17:15.480 --> 02:17:17.680
Oh my God, it's ghost and a woman and a thing.

02:17:17.800 --> 02:17:19.380
And everyone's like, oh, that's a great story.

02:17:19.420 --> 02:17:20.160
You should write about that.

02:17:20.200 --> 02:17:21.500
I'm like, no, no, it's not a story.

02:17:21.560 --> 02:17:22.180
It really happened.

02:17:22.180 --> 02:17:25.440
But so pretty soon I'm like, no one believes me.

02:17:25.480 --> 02:17:26.580
Everyone's like, oh, you fell back asleep.

02:17:26.760 --> 02:17:27.440
Fell back asleep.

02:17:27.560 --> 02:17:28.040
It was noon.

02:17:28.120 --> 02:17:29.060
I'd been reading the paper.

02:17:29.160 --> 02:17:31.320
Like nobody believes me.

02:17:31.380 --> 02:17:34.040
So I just kind of start like not even thinking about it anymore.

02:17:34.680 --> 02:17:36.620
And I'm like, I'm not even going to do the script anymore.

02:17:37.760 --> 02:17:42.460
And then one day a friend calls me up and he goes, hey, remember that story you told me a couple of weeks ago?

02:17:42.460 --> 02:17:43.260
I go, yeah.

02:17:43.780 --> 02:17:49.140
And he goes, I want you to walk down the street to Soap Plant, which was like this esoteric book and novelty store.

02:17:49.680 --> 02:17:51.380
I lived right off Melrose at the time.

02:17:52.180 --> 02:17:56.260
And pick up the new Whole Earth catalog and turn to page 187.

02:17:56.680 --> 02:17:57.420
I'm like, why?

02:17:57.500 --> 02:17:59.400
And he goes, just do it and then call me back.

02:18:00.340 --> 02:18:01.000
I go, okay.

02:18:01.380 --> 02:18:02.340
So I walk down.

02:18:02.420 --> 02:18:03.080
I'm like, go in.

02:18:03.140 --> 02:18:04.520
I find the new Whole Earth catalog.

02:18:04.660 --> 02:18:07.320
For your audience who doesn't know, this was pre-internet.

02:18:07.400 --> 02:18:08.360
This was the internet.

02:18:08.440 --> 02:18:10.120
This was like an analog version of the internet.

02:18:10.120 --> 02:18:15.100
Someone went and collected all the coolest short stories and pamphlets and whatnot, things that were out of print.

02:18:15.300 --> 02:18:20.360
And you'd find what you wanted and send in your money and they'd send you back, you know, the hard copy.

02:18:21.080 --> 02:18:22.200
So I'm flipping through.

02:18:22.320 --> 02:18:24.240
I find the page and I'm like, okay, what's on this?

02:18:24.240 --> 02:18:31.500
And I find this book of out of print ghost stories from Scandinavia in the 15th century.

02:18:32.100 --> 02:18:35.060
And it's like one of the stories is called Witch Rider.

02:18:35.060 --> 02:18:44.740
And it's about this myth of a woman in a tattered sundress who will appear at the foot of your bed, jump on you and steal your soul if you'll let her.

02:18:46.520 --> 02:18:50.300
Now, on one hand you go, oh, well, that's just dumb.

02:18:50.660 --> 02:19:04.820
Except that why was the myth from Scandinavia in the 15th century coming to me in the 20th century in a bungalow apartment in LA on a Tuesday at noon?

02:19:06.060 --> 02:19:14.180
And so that, at that moment, the horror of being connected to something so much bigger and so much more random and so much weirder.

02:19:15.160 --> 02:19:19.900
Now, all the fear that I didn't feel before I felt and it went up my spine.

02:19:19.900 --> 02:19:23.500
And I remember just throwing the book like, oh, just, oh, get it away from me.

02:19:24.820 --> 02:19:32.640
So the coda to this sequence is I lived with the weird, like this, that whole experience didn't make any sense to me.

02:19:32.640 --> 02:19:47.020
Because why would the voice that said into my ear, I'm right here, as if, go ahead, have this cool experience waiting for you, then also be the one that says, just look away.

02:19:47.100 --> 02:19:48.340
Like, oh, you've had enough, kid?

02:19:48.440 --> 02:19:49.400
Okay, just look away.

02:19:49.960 --> 02:19:52.800
Like, that was all I could, but that didn't make a lot of sense to me.

02:19:52.800 --> 02:20:00.920
Like, this entity that was, had been mythologized as, like, this horrible thing would be, take pity on a kid, you know?

02:20:00.980 --> 02:20:06.240
Like, and it wasn't until last year I was talking to a friend who was a psychic medium.

02:20:06.500 --> 02:20:12.960
I start to tell her a story and she goes, oh, that was your, that was your guardian angel or your higher self or whatever you want to call it talking to you.

02:20:13.460 --> 02:20:14.200
I'm like, really?

02:20:15.160 --> 02:20:15.820
I don't understand.

02:20:15.900 --> 02:20:17.380
Like, why did they say, I'm right here?

02:20:17.660 --> 02:20:22.800
Because they knew you were about to have an experience that you'd be challenged with and they wanted to let you know that you weren't alone.

02:20:24.900 --> 02:20:25.300
Wow.

02:20:25.860 --> 02:20:28.120
And I, and that's why they said, just look away.

02:20:29.240 --> 02:20:29.600
Whoa.

02:20:29.860 --> 02:20:32.100
Because you would have died right there on that bed.

02:20:35.240 --> 02:20:35.640
Whoa.

02:20:37.040 --> 02:20:37.400
Dude.

02:20:37.600 --> 02:20:38.000
I know.

02:20:38.160 --> 02:20:38.780
I know.

02:20:38.780 --> 02:20:41.660
So that's the kind of stuff that I've been.

02:20:42.300 --> 02:20:48.800
I have to ask you, because you mentioned this before we started rolling, you also saw a Nordic alien?

02:20:49.900 --> 02:20:50.200
I did.

02:20:50.600 --> 02:20:52.160
Where did you see a Nordic alien?

02:20:52.260 --> 02:20:53.160
On Orcas Island.

02:20:53.440 --> 02:20:53.680
Okay.

02:20:53.920 --> 02:20:55.080
I was visiting a friend there.

02:20:55.120 --> 02:20:56.020
I'll keep this one short.

02:20:56.300 --> 02:21:06.760
I was visiting a friend there and I woke up the next morning after we were talking about a bunch of stuff and he'd gone down to the store, which is quite a ways away from his property to get some food.

02:21:06.760 --> 02:21:08.700
And so I'm like, oh, it's a beautiful day.

02:21:08.740 --> 02:21:11.400
I'm going to take a walk on his property at like 20 acres in the woods.

02:21:11.520 --> 02:21:16.900
So I start walking and I come over this ridge and there'd been no one out.

02:21:17.040 --> 02:21:29.940
And all of a sudden there's this person who literally looks like a male model, like a Scandinavian male model with kind of longish blonde hair in a weird kind of more like European clothes, whatever.

02:21:29.940 --> 02:21:33.620
And they say, hello, Brent.

02:21:34.200 --> 02:21:36.900
Like they're about 20 feet, a little bit further down the hill.

02:21:37.380 --> 02:21:40.980
And I'm thinking, okay, I did not see his mouth move.

02:21:41.520 --> 02:21:43.080
First of all, how's he know my name?

02:21:43.560 --> 02:21:45.380
Secondly, I did not see his mouth move.

02:21:45.740 --> 02:21:48.020
And I was like, hello.

02:21:48.020 --> 02:21:53.040
And he said, turn around and walk the other way.

02:21:55.440 --> 02:21:59.480
And he, mouth not moving and he's not, but he's not looking threatening.

02:22:00.540 --> 02:22:03.860
And I kind of was like, got it on it.

02:22:04.260 --> 02:22:05.460
Turn and I walk away.

